This paper proposes a method to improve the accuracy of robustly trained deep neural networks (DNNs) using a ResNets ensemble algorithm. The paper is focused on the field of machine learning, specifically on improving the performance of DNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses ResNets, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also uses mathematical concepts such as optimal control of transport equations and the Feynman-Kac formula, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of DNNs, which is a common topic in the field of computer security, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible sub-category.
